==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English [[ceosan|ċēosan]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|cho͞oz}}, {{IPA|/tʃuːz/}}, {{SAMPA|/tSu:z/}}
*{{audio|en-us-choose.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: '''Homophones''': [[chew]]s
*: [[Rhymes:English:-uːz|Rhymes: -uːz]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|chooses|choosing|chose|chosen}}

# To [[elect]].
#: ''He was '''chosen''' as president in 1990''
# To [[pick]].
#: ''I '''chose''' a nice, ripe apple from the bowl.''
# To [[decide]] to act in a certain way.
#: ''I '''chose''' to walk to work today.''

====Usage notes====
* This is a [[catenative]] verb that takes the ''to infinitive''. See [[Appendix:English catenative verbs]]

